# MAGICKS — Environment variable reference
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) for local development.
# In production these are configured in the Hostinger Build settings
# (Hostinger → magicks.de → Node.js → Environment Variables).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Internal portal (/portal) — Supabase
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Both values come from the Supabase Dashboard:
#   Project Settings → API
#
# - URL is the project's REST endpoint (https://<ref>.supabase.co)
# - The ANON KEY is the *public* anon role key. It is safe to ship
#   in the browser bundle — Row Level Security policies in
#   `supabase/schema.sql` restrict access to a single allowlisted
#   email. NEVER paste the service-role key here, that one bypasses
#   RLS and would grant full DB access to any visitor.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
